61 Burgh, Burch. Something has been said of this. I am sure that R. intended Peterborough, and I think it can be shown that this was Boston’ s usual name for Peterborough. What T. understood by it is uncertain. A house Brooke in Rutland, to which S. Tibba’s bones were translated, is possible. It was an Augustinian priory, a cell to Kenilworth.
